sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant ODHModel as odh-model-controller
    participant Runtime as Runtime Container<br/>(vLLM/Caikit/OVMS)
    participant S3 as Object Storage (S3)
    participant IstioGW as Istio Gateway<br/>(data-science-gateway)
    participant Authorino as Authorino
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Deployment via InferenceService

    User->>Dashboard: Login via OAuth/OIDC
    Dashboard-->>User: Show model serving UI
    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService CR<br/>(model URI, runtime, resources)
    Dashboard->>KServe: InferenceService CR created

    KServe->>KServe: Reconcile: select ServingRuntime,<br/>create Deployment with<br/>storage-initializer init container
    KServe->>Runtime: Create predictor pod

    Note over Runtime: Init container runs
    Runtime->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    S3-->>Runtime: Model files

    ODHModel->>KServe: Watch InferenceService status
    ODHModel->>IstioGW: Create HTTPRoute for external access
    ODHModel->>Authorino: Create AuthPolicy CRD
    ODHModel->>ODHModel: Create Prometheus ServiceMonitor

    Note over Runtime: Model loaded, serving ready
    Client->>IstioGW: POST predict endpoint<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
    IstioGW->>Authorino: Evaluate auth (API key/JWT)
    Authorino-->>IstioGW: Auth passed
    IstioGW->>Runtime: Forward request (HTTP/8080)
    Runtime-->>IstioGW: Prediction result
    IstioGW-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Notebook
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>(PyTorch DDP)
    participant S3 as Object Storage

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 2: Distributed Training with Resource Queuing

    User->>TrainOp: Submit PyTorchJob CR<br/>(resources, training config)
    TrainOp->>TrainOp: Create master + worker pod specs<br/>Set MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE env vars
    TrainOp->>Kueue: Suspend job (Kueue integration)

    Kueue->>Kueue: Evaluate Workload against<br/>ClusterQueue quota + priority
    alt Resources available
        Kueue->>TrainOp: Admit workload (unsuspend)
    else Queue full
        Kueue->>Kueue: Queue workload,<br/>evaluate preemption
        Note over Kueue: Wait for resources...
        Kueue->>TrainOp: Admit workload (unsuspend)
    end

    TrainOp->>Workers: Create pods + headless Service<br/>DNS-based inter-pod communication
    Workers->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Note over Workers: Execute distributed training<br/>(PyTorch DDP / DeepSpeed / FSDP)
    Workers->>S3: Upload trained model<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Workers-->>TrainOp: Report completion status
    TrainOp->>Kueue: Release resources

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant DSPA as DSPA API Server
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant Step as Pipeline Step Containers
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata
    participant S3 as Object Storage
    participant KServe as KServe
    participant CodeFlare as CodeFlare

    Note over User,CodeFlare: Workflow 3: Data Science Pipeline Execution

    User->>DSPA: Create pipeline run<br/>(via kube-rbac-proxy, REST/8888)
    DSPA->>MariaDB: Store pipeline definition<br/>(3306/TCP)
    DSPA->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow CR

    Argo->>Step: Orchestrate DAG execution<br/>Create pod per step<br/>argoexec sidecar for artifacts

    loop Each pipeline step
        Step->>S3: Read/write step artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
        Step->>MLMD: Log metadata<br/>(gRPC via Envoy proxy)
    end

    alt Deploy trained model
        Step->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR
        Note over KServe: See Workflow 1
    end

    alt Distributed computation
        Step->>CodeFlare: Create RayCluster CR
        Note over CodeFlare: Provisions Ray cluster
    end

    Argo-->>DSPA: Workflow completed
    DSPA->>MariaDB: Update run status

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as User / Application
    participant Envoy as Istio Gateway<br/>(Envoy Proxy)
    participant Router as llm-d-router<br/>(EPP - 60+ plugins)
    participant vLLM1 as vLLM Instance 1
    participant vLLM2 as vLLM Instance 2
    participant KVCache as llm-d-kv-cache
    participant Sidecar as llm-d-routing-sidecar

    Note over Client,Sidecar: Workflow 4: LLM Inference with Disaggregated Serving (llm-d)

    Client->>Envoy: OpenAI chat completion request<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
    Envoy->>Router: ext_proc protocol<br/>(routing decision request)

    Note over Router: Execute plugin pipeline:<br/>1. Prefix-cache scoring<br/>2. Load-aware filtering<br/>3. KV-cache awareness<br/>4. Latency prediction<br/>5. Destination selection

    Router-->>Envoy: Set destination header<br/>(selected vLLM instance)

    alt Standard inference
        Envoy->>vLLM1: Forward to selected instance<br/>(HTTP/8080)
        vLLM1-->>Envoy: Streaming response
    end

    alt Disaggregated prefill/decode
        Envoy->>vLLM1: Prefill phase<br/>(HTTP/8080)
        vLLM1->>KVCache: Transfer KV-cache state
        KVCache->>Sidecar: KV-cache event notification
        Sidecar->>vLLM2: Route decode phase<br/>with cached KV state
        vLLM2-->>Envoy: Streaming decode response
    end

    Envoy-->>Client: Streaming JSON response<br/>(HTTPS)

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as User / Application
    participant Envoy as Istio Gateway
    participant AIGW as AI Gateway<br/>Payload Processing
    participant NeMo as NeMo Guardrails
    participant Secret as K8s Secret<br/>(API keys)
    participant Provider as External LLM Provider<br/>(OpenAI/Anthropic/Azure/Bedrock)

    Note over Client,Provider: Workflow 5: External AI Provider Access via MaaS Gateway

    Client->>Envoy: OpenAI-format request<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Envoy->>AIGW: ext_proc protocol

    AIGW->>AIGW: Resolve ExternalModel<br/>to ExternalProvider mapping

    AIGW->>NeMo: Apply input guardrails<br/>(content safety, PII detection)
    NeMo-->>AIGW: Input validated

    AIGW->>AIGW: Translate API format<br/>(OpenAI to Anthropic/Azure/Bedrock)

    AIGW->>Secret: Read API key from<br/>labeled K8s Secret
    Secret-->>AIGW: API key / credentials

    alt AWS Bedrock
        AIGW->>AIGW: Apply AWS SigV4 signing
    end

    AIGW->>Provider: Forward translated request<br/>(HTTPS/443, API key injected)
    Provider-->>AIGW: Provider-format response

    AIGW->>AIGW: Translate response back<br/>to OpenAI format

    AIGW->>NeMo: Apply output guardrails<br/>(content filtering)
    NeMo-->>AIGW: Output validated

    AIGW-->>Envoy: OpenAI-format response
    Envoy-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)
